cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.GT

Reasoning: 
1. cs.AI - The paper proposes a new GAN architecture and training procedure for generating video game levels, which involves modeling non-local dependencies between game objects and counting objects. This falls under the category of artificial intelligence.
2. cs.LG - The paper proposes a modification of the self-attention GAN and a bootstrapping mechanism to improve the performance of GANs in generating video game levels. This falls under the category of machine learning.
3. cs.CV - The paper deals with generating video game levels, which involves processing and analyzing visual data. This falls under the category of computer vision.
4. cs.GR - The paper deals with generating video game levels, which involves graphics and rendering. This falls under the category of computer graphics.
5. cs.GT - The paper proposes a new approach to generating video game levels that involves modeling constraints and generating unique levels. This falls under the category of game theory.
